  <his_func>&lt;p&gt;B. Burlamacchi, born in 1643 in Geneva, came to Amsterdam after the death of his brother Jean in 1664 to continue his trade affairs. In 1690 he acquired the position of senior merchant in the service of the VOC, in which capacity he left Amsterdam in May 1691.&lt;/p&gt;</his_func>
